Shih was born in Hong Kong to a father who was a math professor in Hong Kong and later became an electrical engineer in the United States, and a mother who was an art teacher and a special-education teacher.[4] Shih and her family emigrated to the United States when she was 4, and she grew up in Arlington Heights, Illinois.[1] In elementary school, she was initially placed in special classes for kids with speech impediments because the school did not have a program in English as a second language.[4] In eighth grade, she scored a 1420 on the SAT out of 1600.[5]
